aits discovered Baitshepi’s distinctly maternal ethos and the "spiritual" kinship embodied in the church’s nurturing fellowship practice. Klaits shows that for Baitshepi members, Christian faith is a form of moral passion that counters practices of divination and witchcraft with redemptive hymn singing, prayer, and the use of therapeutic substances. An online audio annex makes available examples of the church members’ preaching and song.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAIDS (Disease)xPatientsxPastoral counseling ofzBotswana. 0aAIDS (Disease)xReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aAIDS (Disease). 0aChristianity. 0aChurch work with the sickzBotswana. 0aDiseases. 0aHIV infections. 0aHumanities. 0aImmunologic diseases. 0aImmunological deficiency syndromes. 0aLentivirus infections. 0aMedicinexReligious aspects. 0aPastoral care. 0aPsychology and religion. 0aPsychology, Applied. 0aReligion. 0aRetrovirus infections. 0aSexually transmitted diseases. 0aSlow virus diseases. 0aSocial ecology. 0aSocial sciences. 0aSociology. 0aVirus diseases. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh  aaids crisis.  aaids.  aanthropology sociology.  aanthropology.  aapostolic congregation.  abaitshepi church.  abotswana.  achristian faith.  achristian nonfiction.  achristianity.  achurch.  adiscussion books.  aethnographers.  aethnography.  afaith and religion.  afellowship.  afieldwork.  ahiv.  ahuman relationships.  ahymns.  aillness and death.  alife and death.  amodern history.  amoral passion.  apower of god.  apower of prayer.  aprayer.  apreaching.  aspiritual kinship.  aspirituality and faith.  atherapeutic substances.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z9783